First ran :

1) sudo apt-get update
2) sudo apt-get install build-essential python-dev

Then installed pip for python : https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/installing/

1) wget https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py
2) sudo python get-pip.py

List of packages
1) RPi.GPIO
2) time
3) Adafruit_BMP.BMP085
4) urlencode
5) urllib2
6) Adafruit_DHT
7) datetime
8) os
9) sys 

datetime, time, urlencode, urlib2, os and sys are usually preinstalled. (Incase they aren't, they can be installed using pip)

Ran

$ sudo pip install 'package name with quotes'

example : sudo pip install RPi.GPIO


Incase there was problem installing the packages they were installed manually. 

First found the github page of the module.
Example : https://github.com/adafruit/Adafruit_Python_DHT
then use git clone to download the module by running :
git clone https://github.com/adafruit/Adafruit_Python_DHT
1) sudo python Adafruit_Python_DHT/setup.py install





